CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 8, 1956, pg. 7, reads: "Gee, Summer's Gone! - James Greenwalt, center and, left to right, Derwood, Daryl, and Duyaine Dunn greeted the first day of the 1956-57 school year with mixed emotions which seemed to reflect the words that 'Gee whiz, Summer's gone and here we are back in school.' - Harris Photo."Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 8, 1956, pg. 3 reads: "First Day - Accompanied by their parents and a teacher, Crescent School youngsters eagerly enter school. No more jacks, no more dolls, just "readin', 'ritin', and 'rithmetic.' - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Derwood Dunn, James Greenwalt, Darryl Dunn, and Duyaine Dunn, standing outside of Crescent School
